r%20freedom%20and%20subjecting%20them%20to%20cruel%20treatment.%20The%20bodies%20of%20the%20deceased%20migrants%20were%20found%20buried%20near%20the%20detention%20site%2C%20and%20three%20individuals%2C%20including%20one%20Libyan%20and%20two%20foreigners%2C%20have%20been%20arrested%20in%20connection%20with%20the%20atrocities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20disturbing%20images%20of%20emaciated%20migrants%20with%20scars%20on%20their%20faces%2C%20limbs%2C%20and%20backs%20have%20been%20shared%20on%20social%20media%2C%20highlighting%20the%20dire%20situation%20faced%20by%20migrants%20in%20Libya.%20The%20country%20has%20struggled%20to%20recover%20from%20the%20chaos%20that%20followed%20the%202011%20NATO-backed%20uprising%2C%20which%20toppled%20longtime%20dictator%20Moamer%20Kadhafi.%20The%20ongoing%20instability%20has%20created%20a%20power%20vacuum%2C%20allowing%20smugglers%20and%20human%20traffickers%20to%20exploit%20vulnerable%20migrants.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELibya's%20strategic%20location%2C%20just%20300%20kilometers%20from%20Italy%2C%20makes%20it%20a%20critical%20departure%20point%20for%20migrants%20seeking%20better%20lives%20in%20Europe.%20However%2C%20this%20journey%20is%20fraught%20with%20peril%2C%20as%20migrants%20risk%20their%20lives%20crossing%20the%20Mediterranean%20Sea.%20The%20treatment%20of%20migrants%20and%20refugees%20in%20Libya%20has%20long%20been%20a%20subject%20of%20criticism%2C%20with%20rights%20groups%20accusing%20authorities%20of%20extortion%2C%20slavery%2C%20and%20other%20forms%20of%20abuse.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20similar%20incident%20last%20month%2C%20two%20individuals%20were%20arrested%20for%20torturing%20and%20detaining%20263%20irregular%20migrants%20in%20El%20Wahat%2C%20eastern%20Libya.%20The%20prosecution%20alleged%20that%20the%20migrants%20were%20held%20captive%20to%20extort%20ransoms%20from%20their%20families%2C%20with%20demands%20ranging%20from%20%2410%2C000%20to%20%2417%2C000.%20Furthermore%2C%20in%20March%20last%20year%2C%20a%20mass%20grave%2