u%20go%20to%20that%20restaurant%2C%20I%20cannot%20join%20you%2C%26quot%3B%20I%20said%20to%20my%20aunt%20over%20the%20phone.%20At%20the%20time%2C%20I%20knew%20the%20restaurant%20my%20aunt%20and%20the%20group%20she%20was%20with%20was%20planning%20to%20dine%20at%20wasn't%20going%20to%20work%20for%20me.%20I%20had%20previously%20contacted%20the%20restaurant%20and%20someone%20on%20staff%20informed%20me%20that%20they%20couldn't%20guarantee%20that%20my%20food%20would%20be%20free%20of%20gluten.%20For%20me%2C%20it%20was%20a%20hard%20no.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20have%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fdiet-nutrition%2Fceliac-disease-symptoms%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eceliac%20disease%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20which%20is%20a%20chronic%20autoimmune%20condition%20that%20affects%20the%20small%20intestine%2C%20which%20can%20be%20damaged%20when%20it%20comes%20into%20contact%20with%20gluten.%20I%20was%20diagnosed%20a%20few%20weeks%20before%20I%20turned%2018.%20While%20it%20wasn't%20a%20desired%20birthday%20gift%2C%20over%20the%20last%20eight%20years%20I've%20learned%20to%20live%20with%20this%20issue%20comfortably.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20treatment%20for%20this%20condition%20is%20straightforward%3A%20avoid%20eating%20gluten%20for%20all%20your%20life.%20While%20this%20might%20sound%20drastic%2C%20it%20is%20feasible.%20Most%20foods%2C%20like%20veggies%20and%20fruit%2C%20as%20well%20as%20protein%20and%20healthy%20fat%20sources%2C%20naturally%20don't%20contain%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthings-i-wish-i-knew-before-i-went-gluten-free-2018-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Egluten%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20There%20are%20a%20good%20number%20of%20gluten-free%20options%20among%20cereals%20and%20pseudocereals%20too%2C%20such%20as%20rice%2C%20corn%2C%20buckwheat%2C%20and%20amaranth.%20I%20just%20have%20to%20be%20proactive%20and%20know%20what%20I'm%20putting%20into%20my%20body.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EStill%2C%20when%20dining%20out%20with%20other%20people%20or%20in%20other%20people's%20homes%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-is-a-gluten-intolerance-2018-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eceliac%20disease%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20can%20be%20psychologically%20challenging.%20Here's%20how%20I've%20learned%20to%20manage%20some%20common%20scenarios.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2236e944c1-2931-4981-b61f-f2a51d61dfce%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhen%20dining%20out%20I%20research%20and%20ask%20for%20information%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhere%20I%20live%20in%20Italy%2C%20the%20AIC%20(Italian%20Celiac%20Society)%20maintains%20a%20list%20of%20certified%20venues%20that%20I%20know%20will%20have%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftraveling-and-eating-on-a-gluten-free-diet-2018-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Egluten-free%20options%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20However%2C%20I%20often%20want%20to%20dine%20somewhere%20else%20or%20I%20am%20not%20the%20one%20deciding%20the%20location.%20While%20AIC-certified%20venues%20are%20safer%20choices%20for%20people%20with%20celiac%20disease%2C%20I%20have%20become%20quite%20comfortable%20going%20to%20non-certified%20restaurants%2C%20provided%20that%20I%20check%20in%20with%20them%20beforehand.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhen%20dining%20out%20somewhere%20I%20haven't%20been%20before%2C%20I%20usually%20call%20ahead%20to%20inform%20them%20I%20have%20celiac%20disease%20and%20inquire%20about%20gluten-free%20options.%20I%20also%20look%20at%20the%20restaurant's%20website%20to%20explore%20its%20menu%2C%20which%20sometimes%20it%20indicates%20potential%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmy-food-allergies-have-eased-but-eating-is-still-complicated-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eallergens%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20or%20states%20that%20the%20restaurant's%20staff%20is%20trained%20to%20help%20customers%20with%20intolerances.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESome%20months%20ago%20I%20was%20invited%20to%20a%20friend's%20birthday%20party.%20When%20I%20called%20the%20restaurant%20we'd%20be%20attending%2C%20the%20staff%20seemed%20knowledgeable%20about%20celiac%20disease%2C%20which%20was%20a%20good%20sign.%20At%20the%20dinner%20party%2C%20I%20reminded%20them%20of%20my%20condition%20when%20ordering%20a%20seafood%20dish.%20They%20told%20me%20there%20was%20an%20element%20with%20gluten%20but%20they%20would%20tell%20the%20chef%20to%20prepare%20the%20dish%20without%20it%20and%20to%20take%20special%20care.%20This%20made%20me%20feel%20cared%20for%2C%20which%20is%20always%20a%20pleasant%20experience.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22cd328ad7-c8b3-4b52-b929-c61416049738%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhen%20eating%20at%20someone%20else's%20house%20I%20explain%20my%20dietary%20needs%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhen%20dining%20at%20a%20friend's%20home%2C%20I%20often%20call%20to%20discuss%20the%20menu%20ahead%20of%20time.%20If%20other%20guests%20are%20having%20food%20with%20gluten%2C%20like%20pasta%2C%20I%20either%20plan%20to%20skip%20that%20course%2C%20ask%20for%20an%20alternative%2C%20or%20offer%20to%20bring%20something%20.%20If%20I%20have%20any%20doubts%20about%20a%20dish%2C%20I%20know%20to%20ask%20the%20host%20for%20clarification.%20If%20they%20are%20uncertain%20about%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsurprising-foods-with-gluten-2015-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eingredients%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20I%20ask%20them%20if%20they%20checked%20if%20it%20contains%20gluten%20when%20they%20bought%20it.%20Based%20on%20their%20answer%2C%20I%20make%20my%20choice.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENow%2C%20my%20friends%20and%20family%20know%20that%20I%20have%20celiac%20disease%2C%20so%20I%20don't%20have%20to%20explain%20my%20dietary%20needs%20in-depth%20anymore.%20Still%2C%20I%20sometimes%20should%20be%20more%20thorough%2C%20specifically%20telling%20them%20that%20clean%20cookware%20is%20needed%20and%20that%20they%20should%20wash%20their%20hands%20if%20they%20have%20touched%20food%20with%20gluten.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d7503db5-0ec7-41d6-984b-c9528428eb27%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EI'm%20not%20afraid%20to%20stand%20up%20for%20myself%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDuring%20that%20call%20with%20my%20aunt%2C%20we%20decided%20to%20change%20the%20venue%20and%20go%20to%20one%20of%20my%20favorite%20restaurants%2C%20an%20AIC-certified%20venue%20where%20almost%20all%20dishes%20have%20a%20gluten-free%20version%20(even%20pizza!).%20She%20assured%20me%20it%20wasn't%20an%20issue%20if%20this%20made%20me%20feel%20safer%2C%20so%20I%20enjoyed%20a%20delightful%20dinner%20with%20my%20cousin%2C%20my%20aunt%2C%20and%20a%20friend.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fceliac-disease-learned-to-stand-up-for-myself-dining-out-2025-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1739126103000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67a65a99eb4be2fff9a3f8a7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fceliac-disease-learned-to-stand-up-for-myself-dining-out-2025-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22I%20was%20diagnosed%20with%20celiac%20disease%20at%2018.%20Since%20then%2C%20I've%20had%20to%20set%20and%20stick%20to%20clear%20boundaries%20when%20dining%20with%20my%20family%20and%20friends.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Nicole%20Benedettini)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A6%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%